WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.100 --> 00:00:07.400
 Grated okonomiyaki, low sugar okonomiyaki recipe. 

00:00:13.400 --> 00:00:23.400
 Ingredients 2 servings pork thin sliced ​​meat 100 g egg 2 pieces eggplant 1 bean sprouts 200 g leek 1/2 bunch (100 g) long shrimp 70 g dried shrimp 2 tablespoons flour 6 tablespoons flour 2 oil teaspoons salad oil , Green onion, red ginger 

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:39.400
 Grate the chopsticks and mix the eggs and flour. 

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:09.400
 Cut leek into 2-3 cm and mix, 

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:21.400
 Cut the bean sprouts and mix them. 

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:40.400
 The chikuwa is cut into 1 cm wide and divided into 4 equal parts. 

00:01:52.400 --> 00:02:01.400
 Add the dried shrimp and mix it. 

00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:13.400
 Put 1 teaspoon of salad oil in a frying pan and cook on medium heat between medium and low heat. When it gets hot, add half of the dough and spread it to about 15 mm thick. 

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:25.400
 Place half of the pork slices on top and bake for 3 to 4 minutes. 

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:37.400
 Return and bake the other side for 3 to 4 minutes. 

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:59.400
 The two sides are nicely browned and transferred to a plate when the heat passes. I will bake one more piece of this. 

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:12.400
 Pick your favorite sauce, mayonnaise, green paste, red ginger and minced green onion. 

00:03:56.400 --> 00:04:02.400
 It is the completion of eel sprouts okonomiyaki! 

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:14.400
 It is a light texture with a flaky flavor. The beer tastes good. 

